<para id="fs-idp143538880">(b) <m:math><m:mrow>

<m:msubsup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.5em"/><m:mn>92</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>239</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mtext>U</m:mtext>

</m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-idp134068000">(c) <m:math><m:mrow>

<m:msubsup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>20</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>38</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mtext>Ca</m:mtext>

</m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-idp137322448">(d) <m:math><m:mrow>

<m:msubsup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mtext>H</m:mtext>

</m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-idp179430752">(e) <m:math><m:mrow>

<m:msubsup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.5em"/><m:mn>94</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>245</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mtext>Pu</m:mtext>

</m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
</exercise><exercise id="fs-idp54341232"><problem id="fs-idp90959696">
<para id="fs-idm5650336">The following nuclei do not lie in the band of stability. How would they be expected to decay?</para>
<para id="fs-idp92587472">(a) <m:math><m:mrow>

<m:msubsup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>15</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>28</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mtext>P</m:mtext>

</m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-idm20106176">(b) <m:math><m:mrow>

<m:msubsup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.5em"/><m:mn>92</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>235</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mtext>U</m:mtext>

</m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-idm22275216">(c) <m:math><m:mrow>

