<exercise id="fs-idp87827184">
<problem id="fs-idp89910000">
<para id="fs-idm43525136">Define the term half-life and illustrate it with an example.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idp2203040">
<para id="fs-idp25513776">Half-life is the time required for half the atoms in a sample to decay. Example (answers may vary): For C-14, the half-life is 5770 years. A 10-g sample of C-14 would contain 5 g of C-14 after 5770 years; a 0.20-g sample of C-14 would contain 0.10 g after 5770 years.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
